Developed a multi-threaded Client-Server architecture using Java Sockets (java.net) to enable real-time, bidirectional communication.

Engineered a Client Handler to manage simultaneous connections concurrently through multi-threading and stream synchronization.

Implemented robust data handling using InputStream and OutputStream for reliable message exchange over specific TCP ports.

Optimized network performance by managing socket lifecycles, port binding, and exception handling to ensure system stability.
